        <div class="container">
            <div class="row">
                <div class="col-md-12">
                    <div class="mu-page-breadcrumb-area">
                        <h2>What is bullying?</h2>
                        <ol class="breadcrumb">
                            <li>@Html.ActionLink("Home", "Index", "Home")</li>
                            <li class="active">@Html.ActionLink("Bullying", "Bullying", "Challenges")</li>
                        </ol>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>
    <!-- End breadcrumb -->

    <section id="mu-course-content">
        <div class="container">
            <div class="row">
                <div class="col-lg-12">
                    <div class="mu-course-content-area">
                        <div class="row">
                            <div class="col-md-9">
                                <!-- start course content container -->
                                <div class="mu-course-container mu-course-details">
                                    <div class="row">
                                        <div class="col-lg-12">
                                            <div class="mu-latest-course-single">
                                                <div class="mu-latest-course-single-content">
                                                    <h2>Bullying</h2>
                                                    <p>Bullying is a common and well-known problem. It’s hurtful for the kids and can impact them for a long time.</p>
                                                    <p>It is when someone or a group of people who have more power than others, and repeatedly use words or actions to hurt them. Bullying can happen anywhere – at home, with friends, in a group, at school, or in the bus.</p>
                                                    <p>Bullying happen in many ways: verbal, physical, social and cyberbullying.</p>
                                                    <p>The following graph shows the proportion of children suffer from bullying in your council area.  </p>
